B. The stock fell 15&ndash;20%. Why? Sellside analysts publish a consensus that everyone can see. But buyside desks (hedge funds, institutions) run proprietary models &mdash; the <em>whisper</em>. Before AVGO earnings, the buyside was pricing in CEO Hock Tan raising the FY27 AI semiconductor target above the published $100B+ figure, probably to $120B+. When he held the line, funds that had positioned for a raise-and-beat unwound. The headline said &ldquo;beat&rdquo; but the actual question is whether AVGO beat the <em>expected magnitude of the beat</em> &mdash; and it didn&rsquo;t. You now own AVGO at a better price than it traded at before those earnings. The business got stronger; the whisper gap created your entry.\n    </p>\n    <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;font-style:italic;\">\n      Also today: <em>beat-and-raise</em> &mdash; the two-word phrase that separates a meh earnings reaction from a rocket; beat the number AND raise the outlook = strongest combo in US equities.\n    </p>\n  </td></tr></table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 24px 24px;border-top:1px solid #f3f4f6;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.6;\">\n    Research output, not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Verify halal compliance quarterly on Zoya or Musaffa. Prices: NVDA/LLY/TSM/AMD Jun 8 2026 close (Yahoo Finance, CNBC, Investing.com); AVGO Jun 9 2026 (CNBC/Investing.com). LLY Retatrutide Phase 3: Eli Lilly press release / BioPharma Dive Jun 8 2026. AVGO Q2 FY26 earnings: CNBC / Motley Fool transcript Jun 3 2026. VRDN PDUFA: BusinessWire / HCPLive. Halal: Musaffa AAOIFI, verified May 11 2026 &mdash; re-verify quarterly. Generated Jun 9 2026, Kuwait time (GMT+3).\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n</td></tr></table>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
